In this section we create a proxy for the MasterPasswordRepository preventing brute force attacks on the master password.
Once the user has entered a wrong password three times, it will be blocked for 1 Minute.
1.) (MasterPasswordRepositorySecurityProxy) extract interface IMasterPasswordRepository from MasterPasswordRepositorySecurityProxy (refactoring too: extract interface)
2.) (Main) Change type of field for MasterPasswordRepository to the interface IMasterPasswordRepository.
3.) (Main) Apply proxy in field initializer for the MasterPasswordRepository
4.) (Main) create class MasterPasswordRepositorySecurityProxy (refactoring tool: create class).
5.) (Main) create ctor for class MasterPasswordRepositorySecurityProxy accepting the interface IMasterPasswordRepository as parameter.
6.) (MasterPasswordRepositorySecurityProxy) Implement logic in MasterPasswordRepositorySecurityProxy.